.TH antimony-export 1  "export " 
.SH NAME
antimony\-export \- Export user profiles
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBantimony export\fR [\fB\-n\fR|\fB\-\-name\fR] [\fB\-d\fR|\fB\-\-dest\fR] [\fB\-f\fR|\fB\-\-feature\fR] [\fB\-s\fR|\fB\-\-system\fR] [\fB\-\-seccomp\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Export user profiles
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-n\fR, \fB\-\-name\fR \fI<NAME>\fR
The name of the profile/feature to export. If absent, export all user\-profiles/features
.TP
\fB\-d\fR, \fB\-\-dest\fR \fI<DEST>\fR
Where to export to. Defaults to current directory
.TP
\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-feature\fR
Target the feature set rather than the profile set
.TP
\fB\-s\fR, \fB\-\-system\fR
Target the system set rather than the user set
.TP
\fB\-\-seccomp\fR
Export the SECCOMP database. Overrides \-\-feature and \-\-system
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
